result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (8th) and Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (8th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Gregory A. Peterson was found guilty of OWI (8th), a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Gregory A. Peterson was found guilty of Resisting/Failing to Stop/Fleeing, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(2t).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court orders the fines, costs, and restitution in this file shall be paid from all funds received into the defendant's prison accounts in accordance with prison policy, not to exceed 25% of gross during the term of initial confinement. If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.
Consecutive to: any other existing sentence.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

records.addlTxt: 11:50 am case called. Defendant Gregory A. Peterson in court with attorney Ryan Scott Ulrich.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Amended Criminal Complaint stated. Attorney Ulrich confirms receipt, waives formal reading. Agreement reached and stated on record by Attorney Blader. Preliminary hearing addressed. Defendant wishes to waive preliminary hearing. Court questions the defendant and accepts waiver of preliminary hearing. Court has read the complaint, finds probable cause a felony has been committed within the courts jurisdiction and enters an order binding the defendant over for trial. Information filed. Attorney Ulrich confirms receipt, waives formal reading.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. State moves to amend Count 3 to Fail to Stop in violation of 346.04(2t) Plea: No Contest to Count 1  & Count 3.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses outright Count 2 and dismisses and reads-in 14TR1975, 14TR1976, & 14TR1977. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Attorney Ulrich. No statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: 8 years Wisconsin State Prison to be served as 4 years Initial Confinement and 4 years Extended Supervision. Consecutive  to any other existing sentence. CONDITIONS of ES: $2300 fine inclusive of costs and $42.50 Blood Draw Fee. 36 month DL revocation, 36 month IID, OWI Assessment, AODA and follow through Terms of Agent. The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Court does not find defendant eligible for CIP but eligible for SAP. Count 3: 9 months WCJ, concurrent to Count 1, Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Court orders 25% inmate earnings. Appeal Rights Given.
